Hibernate:

1. Flush writes SQL but does NOT guarantee durability
2. Commit guarantees durability (ACID property)

Managed → inside Hibernate session (tracked)
Detached → outside session (just data)
Use case → “data travels outside DB boundary”

#Criteria Query

CriteriaBuilder cb = entityManager.getCriteriaBuilder();
CriteriaQuery<User> cq = cb.createQuery(User.class);

Root<User> root = cq.from(User.class);
cq.select(root).where(cb.gt(root.get("age"), 25));

List<User> users = entityManager.createQuery(cq).getResultList();
